summary: This document is a series of fax cover sheets and reservation records from JetBlue Airways to the FBI in response to a subpoena (Case 31E-MM-108062). It provides passenger records for travel between December 29-31, 2004, including reservation details for flights from Palm Beach to New York (JFK). The records show passenger names, addresses, and credit card information, but JetBlue notes it cannot confirm passenger identities due to lack of date of birth or social security data.

events.title: Flight Reservations Subpoenaed
events.description: JetBlue provides reservation records for flights from Palm Beach (PBF) to New York (JFK) on December 30, 2004, and January 3, 2005, in response to an FBI subpoena.

events.title: Initial Subpoena Response
events.description: JetBlue Airways sends initial passenger records via fax to the FBI in response to subpoena Case 31E-MM-108062.

locations: Federal Bureau of Investigation, 505 S. Flagler Drive #500, West Palm Beach, FL 33401
keyFacts: The FBI subpoenaed JetBlue for passenger records for travel between December 29 and December 31, 2004, under case number 31E-MM-108062.
JetBlue provided reservation records showing flights from Palm Beach (PBF) to New York (JFK) on December 30, 2004, and January 3, 2005.
The reservation records include a passenger address in Royal Palm Beach, FL 33411, and credit card payment details.
JetBlue explicitly states it cannot confirm passenger identities because its system lacks date of birth or social security information.
The document shows the FBI was actively gathering travel and financial records (credit card numbers) as part of its investigation into Jeffrey Epstein's network in late 2004/early 2005.
